						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone in the temple of Yellamma.</hi></p>						

						<p>Rāmachandra—A.D. 1277.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the <hi rend="bold">7th year</hi> of the reign of <hi rend="bold">Rāmachandradēva, Īśvara, Kārtika śu., Thursday.</hi> The <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> is lost. In the cyclic year <hi rend="italic">Ī1śvara</hi> there were two <hi rend="italic">Kārtikas</hi> and in the <hi rend="italic">śuddha-paksha</hi> of both the months the following <hi rend="italic">tithis</hi> occurred on Thursdays. <hi rend="italic">Adhika-Kārtika S11u.</hi> 2 = <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1277,</hi> September 30. Do. <hi rend="italic">S11u.</hi> 9 = Do. October 7. <hi rend="italic">Nija-Kārtika S11u.</hi> 8 = Do. November 4. Do. <hi rend="italic">S11u.</hi> 14 = Do. Do. 11.</p>						

						<p>In the absence of the exact <hi rend="italic">tithi,</hi> it is difficult to find out the equivalent.</p>						

						<p>It states that <hi rend="bold">[Talli]-Nāyaka</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">[Nā]geya-Rāhuta</hi> died in a battle. The record is much damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
